Your GAP claim was calculated per the contract.
I will be happy to chat with you and explain on the phone your GAP claim calculation, but you decided not to talk to us. 

In short, there is a maximum amount you can finance that is covered. This is true for all GAP companies, the reason is obvious: if there was no maximum amount allowable a person could finance $100,000.00 on a car worth $3000 and when it is written off the payout would be $97000.00 for the GAP. So, now you understand that there is a maximum. This is normal and reasonable, actuaries at an insurance company would never write a GAP contract with an infinite amount allowed to be financed.

Our product covers a maximum of 160% of the price of your vehicle, OR 160% of the RETAIL black book value of the vehicle at the time of the sale, whichever is the lesser,  FYI: We had the highest allowable amount in the industry at 160%, everybody else was at 150% so we have the best coverage available in the industry for allowable amount.

The book value of the Honda when you purchased it was $25,625.00 and you paid more than that, so we go with the lesser, the book value.
